{"title":"Readers’ Rides: Andrew’s Freewheelin’ Crust Bikes Florida Man Singlespeed","link":"https://theradavist.com/readers-rides-andrews-freewheelin-crust-bikes-florida-man-singlespeed/","date":1679058042000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Say what you will about social media and its adverse effects on society but we’ve been served some stunning bikes through our Instagram Explore page over the years and as a result have connected with some genuinely amazing individuals. So maybe it’s not all that bad? Today’s Readers’ Ride is case in point: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ifdogsrunfree/\" target=\"_blank\">Andrew</a>‘s <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/products/florida-man\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Bikes Florida Man</a> looks like something we’d document in our Philly Bike Expo Reportage. Andrew went to town with this one and boy oh boy is it a looker! Without further adieu…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-21-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-20-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-19-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Over the years, I’ve been dreaming up the ideal all-rounder build for myself. Something that kind of blurs the lines between a traditional steel road bike and an old school mountain bike. It would have to be equally well suited to a mix of pavement and dirt surfaces, comfortable, efficient, practical enough to use for daily transportation and still have enough fun factor to keep things exciting on weekend rides!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-22-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Having always enjoyed the simplicity and zen-like aspects of riding a singlespeed drivetrain, I decided to start with the <a href=\"https://crustbikes.com/collections/frames/products/florida-man?variant=44362812326199\" target=\"_blank\">Crust Florida Man</a> frame as a platform. It had the massive tire clearance and tastefully relaxed geometry numbers I was looking for. I wanted the ability to run a set of cushy <a href=\"https://ultradynamico.com/products/mars-race\" target=\"_blank\">650b Ultradynamico Mars tires</a> and also have the option to run voluminous slicks with full coverage fenders to help me get through the wet winter months here in the PNW.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-18-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-17-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-16-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Right out of the box, the FM got me most of the way there! Crust is pumping out some of the coolest stuff these days! The only issue for me was the original version of the FM was designed with a fixed gear drivetrain in mind, with the option for a front brake only. It didn’t have the cantilever brake bosses that I wanted for safely bombing down our steep local hills and tackling some flowy single track trails on the side.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-14-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-13-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The silver lining, though, was that this became an opportunity for me to learn the basics of brazing, something I’d been interested in doing for quite some time! Thanks to everyone who gave tips and resources to help me get started! I added the cantilever brake bosses and built the fork truss from scratch out of 4130. Hopefully this project will act as a stepping stone to building my own frame someday. You gotta start somewhere!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-10-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-11-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The fork truss is a super cool design feature that I’ve always admired in vintage bicycles and motorcycles. This one was built with thin enough diameter tubing that it bends in such a way to allow for the fork blades to flex as they should, while still being rigid enough to help support a large handlebar bag. I brazed on a threaded M5 rack boss to hold a barrel adjuster, acting as a stop for the front brake cable housing.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-09-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>A few little warm tone details like the gorgeous brass barrel adjusters by <a href=\"https://shovelresearch.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Shovel Research</a>, brass headset spacers by Blue Lug and the undeniably excellent <a href=\"https://www.sim.works/products/simworks-by-hoshi-stainless-peregrine-spokes\" target=\"_blank\">Hoshi Peregrine spokes by SimWorks</a> really helped tie everything together. <a href=\"https://wearestuntdoubles.com/finishing-pricing\" target=\"_blank\">Stunt Doubles Color</a> in Seattle, WA did an incredible job on the paint. Having seen some of their work before, I decided to go for the Creative Juices Special and let them do their thing! Very pleased with the result to say the least, I think it suits the character of the build and my personality perfectly!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-12-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>I made my own head tube badge out of a salvaged piece of copper, which I think plays nicely off the hammered copper rivets on my Brooks B-17 saddle. “If Dogs Run Free” is one of my favorite Bob Dylan tunes from his 1970 album New Morning. In a phrase, it’s an encapsulation of my whole philosophy to bike riding. It’s essentially about the carefree nature of rambling around through space and time, for no other reason than the love and freedom of it all.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-08-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-07-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>With no goals or agenda in mind, one is able be fully receptive to each moment as it unfolds, existing truly in the moment heightens the quality of experience and creates a sense of meaning behind the activity. This is a space that has become increasingly difficult to find in our modern lives.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-06-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-05-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-04-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Our mental health is on the decline as so much of our attention is being directed away from the natural experiences of which we evolved and into a new, highly artificial world of engineered experience, one consisting mostly of flashing screens and endless notifications. I believe getting outside and riding a bicycle is one of the easiest ways to break away from all of that and reconnect, even if just momentarily, with what is important.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-02-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>A special thank you to Shawn Crowley, who was generous enough to build me the custom fillet brazed stem for this build!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-03-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>You can find me on <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ifdogsrunfree/\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> if you’d like to see some of my past bike builds and check out what I’m currently up to. Please though, make sure to put down your phone afterwards and get outside!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-23-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Lastly, the Crust Florida Man is the signature frame of Leo Rodgers, who is currently rehabilitating from a bad accident involving him on his bike and an SUV. Here’s a link to the GoFundMe page where you can help him out if you’d like. <a href=\"https://www.gofundme.com/f/leo-rodgers-needs-your-help\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.gofundme.<wbr></wbr>com/f/leo-rodgers-needs-your-<wbr></wbr>help</a></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1706\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?w=2560&amp;quality=75 2560w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Andrews_Cust_FM-01-scaled.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Build Specs:</strong></p>\n<p>Frameset: Crust Florida Man 58cm paint by Stunt Doubles Color<br />\nTruss: IDRF Custom<br />\nHeadset: White Industries 1-1/8”<br />\nSpacers: Blue Lug Brass + Nitto<br />\nStem: Fillet Brazed 80mm built by Shawn Crowley<br />\nHandlebars: Crust Towel Rack 630<br />\nTape: Newbaum’s with Nitto plugs<br />\nBrakes: Paul Neo-Retro<br />\nCables: SimWorks Nissen Heritage<br />\nLevers: DIA-COMPE 202<br />\nSaddle: Brooks B-17 Special Titanium<br />\nPost: SimWorks Beatnik 27.2<br />\nCrankset: White Industries Road 172.5mm<br />\nBB: White Industries 113mm<br />\nChainring: White Industries 40t<br />\nPedals: SimWorks Bubbly<br />\nChain: Izumi Super Toughness 3/32”<br />\nFreewheel: White Industries 18t<br />\nHubs: Surly Ultra New 32h<br />\nSpokes: SimWorks Hoshi Peregrine 278mm<br />\nRims: Crust Rim Brake 650b<br />\nTires: Ultradynamico Mars Race 2.2”<br />\nBags: Swift Catalyst + Zeitgeist</p>\n<p> </p>\n<hr />\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>We’d like to thank all of you who <a href=\"mailto:readersrides@theradavist.com\" target=\"_blank\">submitted Readers Rides</a> builds to be shared here at The Radavist. The response has been incredible and we have so many to share over the next few months. Feel free to submit your bike, listing details, components, and other information. You can also include a portrait of yourself with your bike and your Instagram account! Please, shoot landscape-orientation photos, not portrait. Thanks!</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/readers-rides-andrews-freewheelin-crust-bikes-florida-man-singlespeed/\">Readers’ Rides: Andrew’s Freewheelin’ Crust Bikes Florida Man Singlespeed</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"120889641b1df75bba733d48316a1aff6725aafbd45800a02e15cfb83e08fc55","category":"Cycling"}